entries.title: Celebrities Who Endorsed Crypto, NFTs Land in Legal Crosshairs
entries.description: Prominent endorsers are named as defendants in class-action lawsuits by investors, while agents warn clients away from future deals.

entries.title: Ford Cuts Prices of EV Mustang Mach-E
entries.description: The move comes weeks after Tesla reduced prices on a number of its models.

entries.title: When Your Dog Eats Your Apple AirTag
entries.description: Apple never meant for the devices to track pets, but people put them on their collars anyway. Dogs are beeping, and sometimes landing at vets, where X-rays show the culprit. ‘My God, I hope she didn’t eat it.’

entries.title: Vast Maya Kingdom Is Revealed in Guatemalan Jungle
entries.description: Archaeologists discovered a sprawling network of ancient ruins using laser mapping technology.

entries.title: Memory-Chip Makers Face a Prolonged Price Slump
entries.description: Prices of the chips are expected to keep falling in the first half of 2023, putting more pressure on an industry that has already cut investments and jobs.

entries.title: TravelCenters of America Plans EV Fast-Charger Build-Out
entries.description: The truck-stop and gasoline-filling company plans to join with Electrify America in the build-out.

entries.title: Tesla's Big Price Cuts Spark Backlash
entries.description: Tesla’s decision to slash prices on some vehicles has upset some customers, many of whom paid thousands of dollars more for their cars just weeks earlier.

entries.title: TikTok's Chief to Testify Before Congress in March
entries.description: Shou Zi Chew has agreed to appear before the House Energy and Commerce Committee as Republican lawmakers step up scrutiny of the Chinese-owned video-sharing app.

entries.title: Missing Radioactive Capsule Prompts Search and Concern in Australia
entries.description: In the Australian Outback, authorities are engaged in an unusual search-and-recovery effort. Gone missing is an 8-millimeter-long capsule of radioactive material that can burn or sicken anyone who touches it.

entries.title: Baidu Is Developing Its Own ChatGPT, Aiming to Integrate It Into Search
entries.description: China’s Baidu is developing an AI-powered chatbot similar to OpenAI’s popular ChatGPT and plans to integrate it into its main search engine in March, people familiar with the matter said.
